body_text.text:
Our model's biological parameters derive mostly from observations of early SARS patients in Hong Kong (Lee et al., 2003; Tsang et al., 2003). We estimated time-varying control parameters by minimizing sums of squared differences between cumulative model hospitalizations, χE+φPIP+φRIR—where χE are those hospitalized from quarantine and φI from successive symptomatic stages, denoted by subscripts—and probable cases admitted to Tan Tock Seng Hospital (TTSH). We estimated these parameters twice, once from the first 30 days of hospital admissions (Table 1
), before quarantine began, and once from admissions during the entire outbreak (Table 2
).
